{"word":"πανώλης","slug":"πανώλης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πανώλης</b></el> <el>(πᾰν-ώλης, ες) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὄλλυμι'><el>ὄλλυμι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>= <a href='S:πανώλεθρος'><el>πανώλεθρος</el></a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in moral sense, like <el>πανώλεθρος</el> I. 2, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>all-destructive</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}